WEBVTT

00:03.210 --> 00:04.540
Whose baby is that?!

00:09.580 --> 00:11.540
Rest in peace, Quinn.

00:11.540 --> 00:14.080
-Your bones, as promised.
-I didn't have a choice.

00:14.080 --> 00:15.290
Perkins' life...or my freedom.

00:16.080 --> 00:17.420
I have Quinn.

00:17.420 --> 00:19.290
He's weak, old,
grasping for power.

00:19.290 --> 00:20.920
Bess Wallace
wore this hairpin.

00:20.920 --> 00:22.500
You killed a teenage girl!

00:22.500 --> 00:26.040
I want my bones!!

00:26.040 --> 00:27.250
♪♪

00:34.210 --> 00:35.620
♪ "L" ♪

00:35.620 --> 00:40.540
♪ Is for the way
you look at me ♪

00:40.540 --> 00:41.880
♪ "O" ♪

00:41.880 --> 00:46.170
♪ Is for the only one I see ♪

00:46.170 --> 00:47.880
Can I help you?

00:47.880 --> 00:51.210
Just trying
to make up my mind.

00:51.210 --> 00:53.250
Let me know if I can give you
a recommendation.
Mm.

00:53.250 --> 00:54.750
♪ "E" ♪

00:54.750 --> 00:59.250
♪ Is even more than
anyone that you adore can ♪

00:59.250 --> 01:00.620
♪ Love ♪

01:00.620 --> 01:05.170
♪ Is all that I can give
to you ♪

01:05.170 --> 01:07.080
I'll take this one.

01:07.080 --> 01:09.170
I-I can't let you
take that one.

01:09.170 --> 01:11.460
Look at the price.

01:11.460 --> 01:14.460
And we get nothing
but returns and complaints.

01:14.460 --> 01:16.540
That one there
is your man.

01:16.540 --> 01:18.000
Roomy.

01:18.000 --> 01:21.120
Holds just about anything.
Strong. Lasts.

01:21.120 --> 01:23.540
You've made yourself a sale,
sir.

01:23.540 --> 01:25.790
Well, all right.

01:25.790 --> 01:31.540
♪♪

01:31.540 --> 01:33.790
Off on a big vacation,
I hope.

01:33.790 --> 01:36.830
Oh, I'm going
on a big adventure.

01:36.830 --> 01:42.830
♪♪

01:46.880 --> 01:49.120
♪♪

01:49.120 --> 01:50.920
♪ "L" ♪

01:50.920 --> 01:55.250
♪ Is for the way
you look at me ♪

01:55.250 --> 01:56.540
♪ "O" ♪

01:56.540 --> 01:59.290
♪ Is for the only one I see ♪

01:59.290 --> 02:01.500
[ Elevator powers off,
metal clanging ]

02:01.500 --> 02:05.380
♪ "V" is very, very ♪

02:05.380 --> 02:07.710
♪ Extraordinary ♪
Seriously?

02:07.710 --> 02:09.120
♪ "E" ♪

02:09.120 --> 02:12.620
♪ Is even more than
anyone that you adore can ♪

02:13.790 --> 02:15.290
♪ Love ♪

02:15.290 --> 02:19.670
♪ Is all that I can give
to you ♪

02:19.670 --> 02:21.420
♪ Love ♪

02:21.420 --> 02:26.080
♪ Is more than just a game
for two ♪

02:26.080 --> 02:28.920
♪ Two in love can make it ♪

02:28.920 --> 02:31.330
♪ Take my heart and... ♪

02:31.330 --> 02:32.120
Something borrowed.

02:43.000 --> 02:44.750
Oh!

02:44.750 --> 02:45.790
What?

02:53.250 --> 02:55.170
Hello?!

02:55.170 --> 02:56.790
I need help!

02:56.790 --> 02:57.880
I need...

02:57.880 --> 03:00.500
Someone!

03:00.500 --> 03:03.250
If you can hear me!

03:03.250 --> 03:05.620
Please! Hello?!

03:24.040 --> 03:25.710
You.

03:25.710 --> 03:28.420
This was...

03:28.420 --> 03:31.580
Are you
out of your freaking mind?

03:31.580 --> 03:34.000
I am 700 months pregnant,
it is my wedding day,

03:34.000 --> 03:36.710
and you chained me to a wall?!

03:36.710 --> 03:40.170
My team is coming.

03:40.170 --> 03:42.500
They're the best trackers
alive. You know that.

03:42.500 --> 03:44.040
They'll find you,
and when they do --

03:44.040 --> 03:45.880
I've constructed
quite the bunker.

03:45.880 --> 03:47.420
That door?

03:47.420 --> 03:49.000
Solid titanium.

03:49.000 --> 03:50.920
Walls?
Soundproof.

03:50.920 --> 03:53.000
Oh, and your friends?

03:55.500 --> 03:56.750
She ran, Liv.

03:56.750 --> 03:58.250
She left her ring behind.

03:58.250 --> 04:01.000
They think you had cold feet.
Ran off.

04:03.620 --> 04:04.920
Liv sent you?

04:04.920 --> 04:07.540
To what?
Shut me up?

04:07.540 --> 04:08.540
Is that it?

04:08.540 --> 04:09.790
Are you here to kill me?
Are you --

04:09.790 --> 04:10.790
Are you going to kill me?!

04:10.790 --> 04:12.210
Did she send you here
to kill me?!

04:12.210 --> 04:13.580
Are you?!
Are you here to kill me?

04:13.580 --> 04:16.620
If you don't shut the hell up
and listen, yes!!

04:17.670 --> 04:19.210
Calm down.

04:19.210 --> 04:22.000
You're B613,
for God's sakes.

04:24.920 --> 04:26.580
We never killed
pregnant women.

04:27.830 --> 04:29.580
In B613.
Mothers and children first.

04:29.580 --> 04:30.710
That's the rule.

04:32.620 --> 04:33.960
Olivia did not send me.

04:33.960 --> 04:35.500
You're currency
for my freedom.

04:35.500 --> 04:38.330
I will trade you to Olivia,
and this will all be over.

04:38.330 --> 04:40.880
You will be out of here
tonight.

04:42.880 --> 04:44.210
There's the bathroom.

04:44.210 --> 04:46.080
I'll be back
in a few hours.

04:46.080 --> 04:50.210
♪♪

04:55.540 --> 04:56.750
Ohh.

05:09.580 --> 05:11.420
Wish me luck.

05:22.330 --> 05:24.460
What?

05:24.460 --> 05:26.080
Hm.

05:26.080 --> 05:28.960
There's an Oscared filet
as the special tonight.

05:28.960 --> 05:29.790
Doesn't that sound good?

05:29.790 --> 05:31.880
Quinn Perkins is missing.

05:31.880 --> 05:33.080
I don't have time
for you.

05:33.080 --> 05:34.460
So what?

05:34.460 --> 05:35.920
What is it
that's so urgent that I --

05:35.920 --> 05:38.120
I have Quinn Perkins.

05:38.120 --> 05:39.500
What?

05:39.500 --> 05:41.460
I have Quinn.

05:41.460 --> 05:43.170
She's mine.

05:45.540 --> 05:47.210
Where is she?

05:50.000 --> 05:52.920
♪♪

05:52.920 --> 05:56.000
There are people.
We've been worried.

05:56.000 --> 05:58.330
Tell me where she is
and then tell me why you --

05:58.330 --> 06:02.000
That reckoning
that I said is coming?

06:02.000 --> 06:05.250
That reckoning is here.

06:05.250 --> 06:06.830
Quinn Perkins...

06:06.830 --> 06:08.460
the one person
that can take you down.

06:08.460 --> 06:11.330
The one person that knows about
your new assassination hobby.

06:11.330 --> 06:14.380
The one person
that you would never kill.

06:14.380 --> 06:16.670
Your reckoning.

06:16.670 --> 06:21.670
I have Quinn Perkins,
the key to my freedom.

06:21.670 --> 06:24.250
Checkmate.

06:24.250 --> 06:27.330
♪♪

06:27.330 --> 06:32.120
I want my bones back.

06:32.120 --> 06:34.210
I win, you lose.

06:34.210 --> 06:35.960
-Mnh-mnh.

06:35.960 --> 06:37.580
Even trade.

06:37.580 --> 06:39.960
You give me my freedom.
Return my bones.

06:39.960 --> 06:41.380
I give you Quinn Perkins.

06:41.380 --> 06:42.540
Or what?

06:45.250 --> 06:46.620
You'll kill her?

06:46.620 --> 06:49.920
You took my dinosaur,
Olivia.

06:49.920 --> 06:51.620
That's war.

06:51.620 --> 06:53.210
My plan
is to kill Quinn Perkins

06:53.210 --> 06:56.420
unless I get back
what you stole.

06:56.420 --> 06:58.540
You're her friend.

06:58.540 --> 07:02.460
You're
her child's godmother.

07:02.460 --> 07:04.540
I'm giving you a chance
to save them both.

07:11.330 --> 07:14.710
You're pathetic.

07:14.710 --> 07:18.710
You won't hurt a hair
on Quinn's head.

07:18.710 --> 07:23.080
You won't do anything
until I say "do something."

07:23.080 --> 07:25.250
You don't make the decisions.
You don't think.

07:25.250 --> 07:27.500
You don't make moves.
I am in charge here.

07:27.500 --> 07:29.330
You will hear from me

07:29.330 --> 07:31.250
when I decide
you will hear from me.

07:31.250 --> 07:33.750
Until then,
you don't touch Quinn.

07:33.750 --> 07:35.120
You stay put.

07:35.120 --> 07:39.420
♪♪

07:39.420 --> 07:41.830
And you wait

07:41.830 --> 07:44.960
to be told what to do.

07:46.790 --> 07:48.380
I'm not bluffing.

07:48.380 --> 07:54.380
♪♪

07:54.830 --> 07:57.500
Don't ever waste my time
like this again.

07:57.500 --> 08:03.540
♪♪

08:06.830 --> 08:12.830
♪♪

08:16.830 --> 08:22.830
♪♪

08:26.830 --> 08:32.830
♪♪

08:36.790 --> 08:39.960
♪♪

08:41.960 --> 08:47.960
♪♪

08:51.920 --> 08:55.920
♪♪

08:58.710 --> 09:00.880
♪♪

09:00.880 --> 09:02.710
Three days.

09:02.710 --> 09:04.420
If I don't get my bones back,
if I don't get my freedom,

09:04.420 --> 09:06.830
I will kill that girl!

09:06.830 --> 09:12.830
♪♪

09:16.830 --> 09:19.500
♪♪

09:26.120 --> 09:28.420
[ Man speaking indistinctly
on P.A. ]

09:32.040 --> 09:34.580
Must've been
a short trip.

09:34.580 --> 09:35.670
Yes. It was.

09:38.080 --> 09:39.500
Quite a variety.

09:39.500 --> 09:42.040
I...

09:42.040 --> 09:43.620
They all look the same
to me.

09:43.620 --> 09:45.500
I...
Anything you like?

09:45.500 --> 09:46.830
Color

09:46.830 --> 09:48.710
Well, what about this one?

09:48.710 --> 09:50.290
It's a popular choice.

09:50.290 --> 09:51.290
But?

09:53.920 --> 09:55.620
Oh, is this serious?

09:55.620 --> 09:57.080
It is.

09:57.080 --> 09:59.460
I mean, why would anything
cost that much

09:59.460 --> 10:02.380
if you can't drive it,
shoot it, or

10:02.380 --> 10:03.830
What is wrong with people?

10:03.830 --> 10:06.670
Snooty D.C. types drive down
here in their electric cars

10:06.670 --> 10:08.710
with their tiny hairless dogs,
and they buy this one

10:08.710 --> 10:10.290
because
it's the most expensive

10:10.290 --> 10:11.920
to make their
so-called friends jealous.

10:11.920 --> 10:13.460
Mm.

10:13.460 --> 10:15.000
I'm...

10:15.000 --> 10:16.880
I'm in over my head here.

10:16.880 --> 10:18.880
Just tell me what to get.

10:18.880 --> 10:20.500
Okay. All right.

10:20.500 --> 10:21.920
Who's the mama?

10:21.920 --> 10:23.750
We talking wife?
Girlfriend?

10:23.750 --> 10:24.960
Second wife?

10:24.960 --> 10:27.420
My daughter.

10:27.420 --> 10:29.750
Well, congratulations,
Grandpa.
Mm.

10:29.750 --> 10:34.040
♪♪

10:38.670 --> 10:40.710
♪♪

10:40.710 --> 10:42.830
Okay, you said
you'd be back last night.

10:42.830 --> 10:45.210
I'm starving.

10:45.210 --> 10:47.460
I need to eat on a schedule,
you know.

10:47.460 --> 10:49.120
And -- And look at me.
I-I cannot stay like this.

10:49.120 --> 10:51.540
This is my wedding gown!
And now there's a tear in it!

10:51.540 --> 10:53.540
I need a fresh pair
of underwear.

10:53.540 --> 10:55.710
I-I need food. I need clothes.
I need pillows.

10:55.710 --> 10:57.290
I need
my green pregnancy pill

10:57.290 --> 11:00.170
and my bouncy ball to sit on
because I have hemorrhoids!

11:00.170 --> 11:01.460
I need home.

11:01.460 --> 11:03.120
So let's go.

11:03.120 --> 11:07.580
Okay, unlock me or whatever
so we can go.

11:07.580 --> 11:13.580
♪♪

11:15.790 --> 11:17.920
She said no.

11:17.920 --> 11:19.040
Didn't she?

11:19.040 --> 11:21.460
I bought a crib.

11:21.460 --> 11:24.210
A

11:24.210 --> 11:26.170
A crib?
You bought a freaking crib?

11:26.170 --> 11:27.500
Olivia has asked
for time.

11:27.500 --> 11:28.960
Time?

11:28.960 --> 11:31.040
There is no time!

11:31.040 --> 11:33.080
Olivia is doing
what she always does.

11:33.080 --> 11:35.380
She's handling you.

11:35.380 --> 11:37.880
She's planning,
she's figuring this out.

11:37.880 --> 11:39.420
She won't trade.

11:39.420 --> 11:41.880
If she wouldn't trade last
night, she'll never trade.

11:41.880 --> 11:44.380
She wants to win!

11:44.380 --> 11:45.750
I'm already dead.

11:45.750 --> 11:47.830
And -- And -- And you're
never going to be free.

11:47.830 --> 11:49.750
You'll die
as much a prisoner as me.

11:49.750 --> 11:52.000
It's over for us!

11:52.000 --> 11:53.830
Do you get that?!

11:53.830 --> 11:55.460
You played this all wrong!

11:55.460 --> 11:56.920
Why buy a crib?!

11:56.920 --> 11:59.170
You just killed my baby!

12:01.460 --> 12:04.920
♪♪

12:04.920 --> 12:06.960
Cereal.

12:06.960 --> 12:08.790
And a change of clothes.

12:08.790 --> 12:11.330
♪♪

12:17.290 --> 12:22.250
Before I'll be a slave,
she'll be buried in her grave.

12:22.250 --> 12:26.250
57 hours and counting.

12:33.830 --> 12:36.000
[ "Straighten Up and Fly Right"
plays ]

12:36.000 --> 12:39.880
♪♪

12:39.880 --> 12:41.830
Hi. Hey!

12:45.920 --> 12:47.670
This is a surprise!
Ah.

12:47.670 --> 12:49.580
Marv Heward.
Montell.

12:49.580 --> 12:51.830
Montell Damascus.

12:51.830 --> 12:55.250
It used to be you'd show off
how cheap you paid for a thing.

12:55.250 --> 12:57.580
Now these people
are proud and bragging

12:57.580 --> 13:01.210
only if they've handed over
a big wad of hard-earned cash

13:01.210 --> 13:03.120
to some corporation.

13:03.120 --> 13:05.120
Yeah.
And those corporations?

13:05.120 --> 13:07.000
They don't hire American men.
Mnh-mnh.

13:07.000 --> 13:10.080
They just got factories
full of kids making the stuff

13:10.080 --> 13:12.750
in some warlord,
no-English-speaking country.

13:12.750 --> 13:14.670
Yeah. Where they've
never even heard

13:14.670 --> 13:16.580
of the Pledge of Allegiance.
Yeah.

13:16.580 --> 13:18.670
They're out there giving
our money to the Communists.

13:18.670 --> 13:20.710
Mm.
It's un-American.

13:20.710 --> 13:24.880
When I got out of the service,
I thought I had it made.

13:24.880 --> 13:26.080
Good-paying job.

13:26.080 --> 13:27.290
Factory closes.

13:27.290 --> 13:29.250
Do I complain?
No.

13:29.250 --> 13:31.880
I get a job
driving a truck.

13:31.880 --> 13:35.290
A year ago, they tell me they're
gonna lay off half the fleet.

13:35.290 --> 13:39.000
They don't even grow food
in this country anymore.

13:39.000 --> 13:40.540
I did not know that.

13:40.540 --> 13:42.040
Mm.

13:42.040 --> 13:43.040
You served?

13:43.040 --> 13:45.040
Army. Two tours.

13:45.040 --> 13:46.120
2nd Battalion.

13:46.120 --> 13:47.330
Oh, right.
Yeah.

13:47.330 --> 13:48.750
Did a tour in Nam.

13:48.750 --> 13:49.790
3rd Division.

13:49.790 --> 13:51.920
You see much action?

13:51.920 --> 13:54.500
Well, when we weren't
taking fire from VC,

13:54.500 --> 13:56.080
we were fixing mopeds

13:56.080 --> 13:58.080
and delivering
village girls' babies.

13:58.080 --> 13:59.830
Never a dull moment,
was there?

13:59.830 --> 14:00.920
No.

14:00.920 --> 14:03.420
Can't say I miss it.

14:03.420 --> 14:06.120
Sure, but it beats
looking for work.

14:06.120 --> 14:08.580
♪♪

14:08.580 --> 14:10.000
I have
an employee discount.

14:10.000 --> 14:12.040
Mm?
Yeah.

14:12.040 --> 14:13.670
Next time you need something,
just come on down.

14:13.670 --> 14:14.960
Discount's on me.

14:14.960 --> 14:17.080
Marv, mm...
No.

14:17.080 --> 14:18.250
I couldn't.
Oh, no. I mean it.

14:18.250 --> 14:19.420
In fact, any time.

14:19.420 --> 14:21.250
Any -- Any time you need
to buy something,

14:21.250 --> 14:22.880
just ask for Marv, and
we'll give you that discount.

14:22.880 --> 14:24.040
I'm not...

14:24.040 --> 14:26.000
That's charity!
No.

14:26.000 --> 14:28.380
What? No.
It's -- It's not charity.

14:28.380 --> 14:29.540
You're still paying
for it.

14:29.540 --> 14:31.170
It's just now it's...

14:31.170 --> 14:33.250
it's 40% off.

14:36.170 --> 14:37.500
40%?
Yeah.

14:37.500 --> 14:39.880
Huh.

14:39.880 --> 14:41.790
Couldn't you get in hot water
for that kinda thing?

14:41.790 --> 14:42.920
No, no.

14:42.920 --> 14:44.290
See, you give me the cash,

14:44.290 --> 14:45.920
and -- and I put it
on my debit card.

14:45.920 --> 14:48.790
Discount's yours,
purchase receipt's in my name.

14:48.790 --> 14:50.120
Nobody will know
that Montell Damascus

14:50.120 --> 14:51.420
set foot in the store.

14:51.420 --> 14:52.580
Deal?

14:52.580 --> 14:55.620
♪♪

14:55.620 --> 15:00.580
My daughter could use a whole
load of stuff for the baby.

15:00.580 --> 15:03.000
All right.

15:03.000 --> 15:04.670
Deal.
All right.

15:07.830 --> 15:09.920
You're a great father.

15:09.920 --> 15:11.670
I hope you know that.

15:11.670 --> 15:13.710
She's lucky to have you.

15:16.960 --> 15:20.330
You're a good person.

15:20.330 --> 15:22.620
We're all good people...

15:22.620 --> 15:25.170
when someone gives us
a chance to be.

15:25.170 --> 15:26.540
♪ Straighten up and stay right ♪

15:26.540 --> 15:28.250
Yeah.

15:28.250 --> 15:30.290
Well...

15:30.290 --> 15:32.540
♪ Cool down, papa,
don't you blow ♪

15:32.540 --> 15:34.000
Yeah.
♪ Your top ♪

15:34.000 --> 15:35.830
♪♪

15:35.830 --> 15:37.580
Man: Fly right.

15:39.290 --> 15:40.620
Ohh.

15:42.620 --> 15:47.540
♪♪

15:47.540 --> 15:50.500
Charlie: You wanted to get out
of marrying me that bad, huh?

15:50.500 --> 15:51.750
What?

15:51.750 --> 15:55.580
♪♪

15:58.250 --> 16:02.330
♪♪

16:04.250 --> 16:06.500
♪♪

16:07.750 --> 16:10.670
♪♪

16:14.920 --> 16:16.750
Kick.

16:16.750 --> 16:19.460
Kick, kick, kick, kick,
kick, kick, kick, kick, kick.

16:19.460 --> 16:21.290
Ah.

16:21.290 --> 16:23.880
Oh, there you are.

16:23.880 --> 16:25.750
Just keep kicking, okay?

16:32.120 --> 16:32.830
She sent you
to case the joint?

16:32.830 --> 16:34.040
This game needs to end.

16:34.040 --> 16:34.830
I couldn't agree more.

16:34.830 --> 16:36.000
Unfortunately,

16:36.000 --> 16:36.920
there's still time
on the clock.

16:36.920 --> 16:38.380
22 hours to be precise.

16:38.380 --> 16:40.880
So make your empty threat
or --

16:40.880 --> 16:42.210
She didn't send me.

16:42.210 --> 16:43.420
I came on my own
to warn you

16:43.420 --> 16:45.080
you're not gonna win
this thing.

16:45.080 --> 16:46.540
In fact,
you've already lost.

16:46.540 --> 16:48.330
You forgot who you're dealing
with. What she's capable of.

16:48.330 --> 16:50.920
She's my daughter. I know
exactly what she's capable of.

16:50.920 --> 16:53.080
You don't.
Not anymore.

16:53.080 --> 16:54.880
She's gonna ride this train
to the end of the line,

16:54.880 --> 16:56.620
and if you don't get out
of the way,

16:56.620 --> 16:58.710
you,
and that innocent woman,

16:58.710 --> 17:00.500
and that
innocent woman's child?

17:00.500 --> 17:02.750
You'll all be crushed.
So what should I do, then?

17:02.750 --> 17:05.290
Tuck my tail between my legs
and ask for a job, like you?

17:05.290 --> 17:07.790
Mnh-mnh.
Let her do her worst.

17:07.790 --> 17:09.380
I'll be ready for her.

17:09.380 --> 17:11.500
Maybe not as ready
as you think.

17:11.500 --> 17:17.500
♪♪

17:21.500 --> 17:24.880
♪♪

17:24.880 --> 17:28.040
Not as ready as I...

17:28.040 --> 17:29.620
think.

17:29.620 --> 17:35.620
♪♪

17:39.620 --> 17:45.670
♪♪

17:51.620 --> 17:53.710
♪♪

17:53.710 --> 17:57.250
I have a right to defend myself.
I have a right to fight back!

17:57.250 --> 18:00.710
I am left defenseless!
That girl is left defenseless!

18:00.710 --> 18:02.500
Was I going to kill her?
Maybe!

18:02.500 --> 18:03.920
Will I ever save her now?

18:03.920 --> 18:05.500
We will never know!

18:05.500 --> 18:06.620
This is not a game!

18:06.620 --> 18:08.460
Too far!

18:08.460 --> 18:10.670
Too! Far!

18:10.670 --> 18:13.080
♪♪

18:13.080 --> 18:17.420
♪ The other night, dear,
as I lay sleeping ♪

18:17.420 --> 18:21.330
♪ I dreamt I held you
in my arms ♪

18:21.330 --> 18:25.420
♪ But when I woke, dear,
I was mistaken ♪

18:25.420 --> 18:29.620
♪ So I hung my head and cried ♪

18:29.620 --> 18:31.580
Huck:
Are you gonna do something?

18:31.580 --> 18:35.920
♪ You are my sunshine,
my only sunshine ♪

18:35.920 --> 18:39.500
♪ You make me happy
when skies are gray ♪

18:39.500 --> 18:40.750
Quinn.

18:40.750 --> 18:42.540
♪ You'll never know, dear ♪

18:42.540 --> 18:43.540
Stop it.

18:43.540 --> 18:45.120
♪ How much I love you ♪

18:45.120 --> 18:46.880
Stop it.

18:46.880 --> 18:50.670
♪ Please don't take
my sunshine away ♪

18:50.670 --> 18:52.040
You're embarrassing me!

18:52.040 --> 18:56.500
-Go away!
-You know how this goes.

18:56.500 --> 18:58.710
You've already been down here
for over 48 hours.

18:58.710 --> 19:01.080
And you still have not made
a single attempt to leave.

19:01.080 --> 19:03.500
Do you see the chain?
I can't leave.

19:03.500 --> 19:06.620
I'm out of options.

19:06.620 --> 19:08.920
When you thought that Liv was
the one who blew up that plane,

19:08.920 --> 19:10.620
you didn't tell anyone.

19:10.620 --> 19:13.420
Because I wasn't sure
it was Liv who actually did it.

19:13.420 --> 19:15.960
Okay.
But then you confronted her.

19:15.960 --> 19:17.290
And that made you sure,
right?

19:17.290 --> 19:19.290
You were sure
that it was Liv,

19:19.290 --> 19:21.000
but you still
didn't tell anyone.

19:21.000 --> 19:23.580
Not me. Not Abby.

19:23.580 --> 19:24.880
Not even your fiancé.

19:24.880 --> 19:27.000
What does that have
to do with anything?

19:27.000 --> 19:29.880
The Quinn I know would be
tearing down the walls

19:29.880 --> 19:31.460
trying to get out of here.

19:31.460 --> 19:34.500
Instead you're chilling
on a filthy mattress,

19:34.500 --> 19:37.500
singing lullabies
wildly out of key.

19:37.500 --> 19:38.830
I have a great voice.

19:38.830 --> 19:41.380
You have
a child to think about.

19:41.380 --> 19:43.170
What would you know
about raising a child?!

19:43.170 --> 19:44.580
Where's your kid?!

19:44.580 --> 19:47.080
♪♪

19:47.080 --> 19:49.420
Huck...

19:51.250 --> 19:52.920
Huck, come back.

19:54.540 --> 20:00.330
♪♪

20:00.330 --> 20:02.790
I didn't tell Charlie
about Olivia.

20:02.790 --> 20:05.120
I didn't tell
anyone about Olivia.

20:05.120 --> 20:07.670
If I had told someone,
it would've made it true.

20:07.670 --> 20:10.210
It would've made it real.

20:10.210 --> 20:13.290
That Olivia
isn't Olivia anymore.

20:13.290 --> 20:17.250
Olivia has become
some monster.

20:17.250 --> 20:18.380
Capable of...

20:21.330 --> 20:23.790
And I don't want
to think that about her.

20:25.830 --> 20:29.000
Huck: Liv still has a chance
to do the right thing.

20:29.000 --> 20:31.620
She's still capable
of doing what's right.

20:31.620 --> 20:33.750
But you can't wait.

20:33.750 --> 20:35.080
He's gonna kill you.

20:35.080 --> 20:36.580
Rowan bought me a crib.

20:36.580 --> 20:39.330
He's not going to --
-The crib is for the baby.

20:39.330 --> 20:41.420
Your baby, Quinn.
Not you.

20:41.420 --> 20:47.420
♪♪

20:48.500 --> 20:50.120
Marv.

20:50.120 --> 20:51.750
You sell handguns, right?

20:51.750 --> 20:53.120
Well, yeah.

20:53.120 --> 20:54.580
Can I use your discount
to get one?

20:54.580 --> 20:55.580
You want to get a gun?

20:55.580 --> 20:57.000
Of course.

20:57.000 --> 20:59.330
Baby coming.
Safety and all.

20:59.330 --> 21:01.000
There've been break-ins
in the neighborhood.

21:01.000 --> 21:02.330
I want my family safe.

21:02.330 --> 21:04.750
Wouldn't you?
Don't you?

21:04.750 --> 21:07.500
You have guns?
Of course.

21:07.500 --> 21:09.210
So can we do the thing
where you buy the gun

21:09.210 --> 21:10.880
and I get the discount?

21:10.880 --> 21:15.040
See...that would mean that
the gun would be in my name.

21:15.040 --> 21:17.460
I'd have to register it
to me.
Yes.

21:17.460 --> 21:19.210
And then in three months,
we turn in the paperwork

21:19.210 --> 21:20.830
that says you're selling
the gun to me,

21:20.830 --> 21:22.540
and we transfer
the registration.

21:22.540 --> 21:24.670
Easy.
It's taken care of.

21:24.670 --> 21:25.710
It's handled.

21:25.710 --> 21:27.250
Right?

21:27.250 --> 21:29.170
It's just...

21:29.170 --> 21:31.920
getting a gun like that
is kinda...

21:31.920 --> 21:33.330
It doesn't feel okay.

21:33.330 --> 21:35.120
It's fighting
the corporate system.

21:35.120 --> 21:36.790
Same as ever.

21:36.790 --> 21:39.620
And isn't it our right
to have our guns?

21:39.620 --> 21:42.040
I mean, taking away
our right to arm ourselves

21:42.040 --> 21:44.540
is just what those snooty
D.C. folk are waiting for.

21:44.540 --> 21:45.920
They take our guns,
they take our freedom.

21:45.920 --> 21:47.170
I don't want to be out there

21:47.170 --> 21:48.500
with nothing
to protect my family.

21:48.500 --> 21:50.540
I'm a man, Marv!

21:50.540 --> 21:52.120
Don't you want me to be
just as much of a man

21:52.120 --> 21:53.420
as

21:53.420 --> 21:55.120
O-O-Or...

21:55.120 --> 21:56.620
is there some difference
between us?

21:56.620 --> 21:58.040
I mean, is that something
we should talk about?

21:58.040 --> 21:59.460
No.
No, no, no.

21:59.460 --> 22:01.460
You're -- You're --
You're right.

22:01.460 --> 22:05.210
And -- And I just wanna say,
I-I would never...

22:05.210 --> 22:08.120
Your blood runs red, white,
and blue -- same as mine.

22:08.120 --> 22:11.000
I mean, Oprah says that...

22:11.000 --> 22:14.250
Montell, I-I don't see color.

22:14.250 --> 22:16.670
We're brothers
from another mother.

22:16.670 --> 22:18.500
Yes, Marv.

22:18.500 --> 22:19.620
We are brothers.

22:21.460 --> 22:23.580
Come on,
let's get you that gun.

22:25.540 --> 22:27.290
♪♪

22:30.710 --> 22:33.210
Maybe get
something larger, too.

22:33.210 --> 22:35.620
Some real firepower
to keep you safe.

22:35.620 --> 22:36.790
You think?

22:36.790 --> 22:37.880
Oh, yeah.

22:37.880 --> 22:40.460
A man's
gotta be fully armed.

22:40.460 --> 22:41.580
God bless America.

22:44.250 --> 22:47.290
God bless America, Marv.

22:55.620 --> 22:58.000
♪♪

22:59.380 --> 23:02.080
♪♪

23:02.080 --> 23:05.580
Like I said.
I'm ready.

23:07.670 --> 23:10.000
You want to serve Command?

23:10.000 --> 23:13.040
Tell her come get her girl.

23:13.040 --> 23:18.290
Tell her I am the darker
brother, I am at the table,

23:18.290 --> 23:21.420
I, too, am America,

23:21.420 --> 23:25.920
and she had better recognize
and respect!

23:25.920 --> 23:28.790
Command ain't nothing
but a title.

23:28.790 --> 23:33.120
Father is who I am.

23:33.120 --> 23:39.120
♪♪

23:43.120 --> 23:49.120
♪♪

23:55.290 --> 23:56.750
Yeah. It's me.

23:56.750 --> 23:59.290
Tell Ms. Pope she's gonna want
to see me right away.

23:59.290 --> 24:02.580
...she had better recognize
and respect!

24:02.580 --> 24:05.250
Command ain't nothing
but a title.

24:07.580 --> 24:10.580
♪♪

24:11.790 --> 24:13.210
You summoned me?

24:15.120 --> 24:18.290
Perkins' life
or my freedom.

24:18.290 --> 24:20.120
You don't summon me.

24:20.120 --> 24:22.670
You do not push me
or rush me.

24:22.670 --> 24:25.380
This is serious business.
You have no idea --

24:25.380 --> 24:28.960
Choose one, Olivia.

24:28.960 --> 24:31.920
Perkins' life
or my freedom.

24:31.920 --> 24:35.250
You're not going
to kill me.

24:35.250 --> 24:38.710
♪♪

24:38.710 --> 24:40.830
I don't have to.

24:40.830 --> 24:42.790
Mm.

24:42.790 --> 24:45.120
You won't be able to live with
that girl's blood on your hands

24:45.120 --> 24:47.620
or the blood of the baby
she has inside of her.

24:47.620 --> 24:50.750
No, I mean,
you're not going to kill me.

24:50.750 --> 24:51.920
And you should.

24:51.920 --> 24:54.040
You should kill me.

24:54.040 --> 24:55.120
It's your only way
out of this.

24:55.120 --> 24:56.750
Seriously.

24:56.750 --> 24:59.540
It's what you would tell
anyone else to do.

24:59.540 --> 25:02.500
Eliminate the problem.
Sever the head of the snake.

25:02.500 --> 25:04.080
I am the snake.

25:04.080 --> 25:06.420
I am the problem.

25:06.420 --> 25:08.880
A bullet in my head is
your only chance at freedom.

25:08.880 --> 25:10.830
Good.

25:10.830 --> 25:13.080
Now all you have to do
is pull the trigger.

25:13.080 --> 25:15.580
♪♪

25:15.580 --> 25:18.210
Pull it.

25:18.210 --> 25:20.330
Pull it!

25:20.330 --> 25:25.080
♪♪

25:29.620 --> 25:31.380
If you're not willing
to kill me,

25:31.380 --> 25:33.750
then you have no cards
left to play.

25:33.750 --> 25:36.250
I win. You lose.

25:36.250 --> 25:38.500
You have a soul left,
Olivia.

25:38.500 --> 25:42.670
You will not let
that girl die.

25:44.250 --> 25:46.210
Charlie: Geez.
Take it easy, Robin.

25:46.210 --> 25:47.920
Do you really need
to do this?

25:47.920 --> 25:50.620
I'm sorry, Charlie,
but we're out of options.

25:50.620 --> 25:52.500
Abby: This isn't one
of your better plans.

25:52.500 --> 25:54.750
I don't need your judgment
right now.

25:54.750 --> 25:56.790
What are you gonna do?
Strangle him with that thing?

25:56.790 --> 25:58.290
Pointless. You're still
gonna have these chains

25:58.290 --> 25:59.330
to contend with.

25:59.330 --> 26:01.500
You're the leader.
Think like a leader.

26:01.500 --> 26:02.750
Huck: Abby.

26:02.750 --> 26:04.000
Be nice.

26:04.000 --> 26:05.380
Fine.
Let's all be nice.

26:05.380 --> 26:07.290
Let's all be nice
and watch her die.

26:07.290 --> 26:10.080
Marcus:
What if this is all a test?

26:10.080 --> 26:11.080
What are
you talking about?

26:11.080 --> 26:12.540
I'm talking about Rowan
testing us

26:12.540 --> 26:14.500
to see if we're foolish enough
to try to escape.

26:14.500 --> 26:16.040
He could just be wanting
another reason to kill us.

26:16.040 --> 26:17.540
Rowan: I will kill her.

26:17.540 --> 26:19.040
Olivia:
You think I'm bluffing.
You guys hear that?

26:20.210 --> 26:21.670
Olivia.

26:21.670 --> 26:23.170
She's fighting with Rowan.
Okay.

26:23.170 --> 26:24.250
She could be here
to save you.

26:24.250 --> 26:25.710
I don't know.

26:25.710 --> 26:27.500
What do you think?

26:27.500 --> 26:28.710
I think
if we have any chance

26:28.710 --> 26:30.290
of getting out of here
ourselves,

26:30.290 --> 26:32.250
we're gonna need to move.
Olivia:
I walk out that door,

26:32.250 --> 26:34.580
and you can spend the next
20 minutes waiting to die.
Now.

26:34.580 --> 26:36.790
You're bluffing.

26:36.790 --> 26:40.330
I think
you're the one who's bluffing.

26:40.330 --> 26:42.790
Your judgment is clouded.

26:42.790 --> 26:46.250
Your soft, chewy center
is out.

26:46.250 --> 26:50.420
If I am
who you hope I am,

26:50.420 --> 26:54.540
then killing Quinn and her baby
destroys me for sure.

26:54.540 --> 26:58.080
If I'm already done,
killing her gets you nothing.

26:58.080 --> 26:59.120
You are bluffing.

26:59.120 --> 27:01.040
Your bluff is showing.
I can see it.

27:01.040 --> 27:02.080
Mm. Try me.

27:04.500 --> 27:08.120
If Quinn has to die for the
Republic, then she has to die.

27:08.120 --> 27:10.620
60 seconds.
Starting now.

27:10.620 --> 27:12.210
Your move.

27:14.540 --> 27:16.710
♪♪

27:16.710 --> 27:18.750
Okay.
Here goes nothing.

27:18.750 --> 27:24.750
♪♪

27:26.540 --> 27:28.540
Little to the left, Robin.

27:28.540 --> 27:34.420
♪♪

27:36.540 --> 27:37.210
-Ah!
-Ah.

27:37.210 --> 27:38.040
-Yes!
-Nice.

27:38.040 --> 27:39.960
-Way to go!
-Good job.

27:39.960 --> 27:41.540
Quinn: All right, there's gotta
be something in here I can use.

27:41.540 --> 27:43.540
I know Rowan wouldn't be
dumb enough to leave me a saw

27:43.540 --> 27:45.540
or a gun or a blowtorch,

27:45.540 --> 27:48.500
but if I could just
MacGyver something...

27:48.500 --> 27:54.500
♪♪

27:57.330 --> 27:59.580
Nothing.

27:59.580 --> 28:01.120
There's nothing.

28:06.040 --> 28:11.290
♪♪

28:11.290 --> 28:13.580
5...

28:13.580 --> 28:15.500
4...

28:15.500 --> 28:17.620
3...

28:17.620 --> 28:18.920
2...

28:18.920 --> 28:24.920
♪♪

28:28.040 --> 28:34.040
♪♪

28:38.040 --> 28:39.790
♪♪

28:41.380 --> 28:45.290
♪♪

28:46.710 --> 28:52.750
♪♪

28:56.750 --> 28:59.750
♪♪

29:02.040 --> 29:04.620
♪♪

29:04.620 --> 29:06.670
Aah!

29:06.670 --> 29:10.170
♪♪

29:10.170 --> 29:11.750
Aah!

29:11.750 --> 29:13.710
♪♪

29:15.420 --> 29:16.920
No!

29:18.380 --> 29:20.040
Please.

29:20.040 --> 29:21.420
Please, no.

29:23.420 --> 29:25.460
I'm sorry.

29:25.460 --> 29:27.120
I can't let her win.
Wait.

29:27.120 --> 29:30.210
Wait. Just wait
until my baby is born.

29:30.210 --> 29:31.750
It won't be long now.
I promise.

29:31.750 --> 29:32.830
Please.

29:32.830 --> 29:34.500
Please!

29:34.500 --> 29:39.710
♪♪

29:58.540 --> 30:00.880
Want to see the body?

30:00.880 --> 30:04.210
I've earned my freedom.

30:04.210 --> 30:06.120
Call off your men.

30:14.120 --> 30:17.420
Olivia --
Wait a few days.

30:17.420 --> 30:18.920
Then figure out a way
to bring her back to us.

30:18.920 --> 30:20.210
I can't just...

30:20.210 --> 30:21.880
have her
in some ditch somewhere.

30:21.880 --> 30:23.540
She's Quinn. Huck will
never stop looking for her,

30:23.540 --> 30:25.210
and...

30:25.210 --> 30:27.000
we need to bury her.

31:22.170 --> 31:23.920
Quinn:
You got what you wanted.

31:23.920 --> 31:28.540
Now let me out.

31:28.540 --> 31:30.620
There's gotta be
something in here I can use.

31:30.620 --> 31:32.000
There's nothing.

31:32.000 --> 31:33.120
Rowan:
You are bluffing.

31:33.120 --> 31:34.830
Your bluff is showing.
I can see it.

31:34.830 --> 31:36.790
Olivia: Mm. Try me.

31:36.790 --> 31:40.170
If Quinn has to die for the
Republic, then she has to die.

31:40.170 --> 31:42.000
Abby:
She's not going to kill you.

31:42.000 --> 31:43.670
She gave you your name.
She gave you OPA.

31:43.670 --> 31:46.040
She even gave you Bess Truman's
hairpin, for crying out loud.

31:46.040 --> 31:47.790
She would never let you rot
in this basement.

31:47.790 --> 31:50.000
Um, are you listening
to this?

31:50.000 --> 31:51.880
60 seconds.
Starting now.

31:51.880 --> 31:53.670
She's gonna kill Quinn?

31:53.670 --> 31:55.120
But what about all the stuff
at OPA?

31:55.120 --> 31:56.750
And the hairpin?
That was before.

31:56.750 --> 31:58.170
Before Quinn
became a liability.

31:58.170 --> 31:59.380
-Time check.

31:59.380 --> 32:01.460
-You don't want to know.
-Oh, my God.

32:01.460 --> 32:03.380
This whole time, I've been
waiting for her to save me,

32:03.380 --> 32:05.170
but she already has.

32:08.460 --> 32:11.380
Sorry, Mrs. Truman.

32:11.380 --> 32:12.670
Come on.

32:13.830 --> 32:16.540
♪♪

32:18.460 --> 32:20.040
Aah!

32:20.040 --> 32:21.830
Aah!

32:24.250 --> 32:26.960
Please!

32:30.250 --> 32:34.750
♪♪

32:37.290 --> 32:43.290
♪♪

32:47.290 --> 32:49.580
Shh.

32:49.580 --> 32:55.580
♪♪

32:59.580 --> 33:04.920
♪♪

33:09.380 --> 33:14.960
♪♪

33:14.960 --> 33:16.920
Rowan:
Want to see the body?

33:16.920 --> 33:18.790
I've earned my freedom.

33:18.790 --> 33:22.170
Call off your men.

33:22.170 --> 33:23.750
Olivia --
Olivia: Wait a few days.

33:23.750 --> 33:25.790
Then figure out a way
to bring her back to us.

33:25.790 --> 33:28.000
I can't just...have her
in some ditch somewhere.

33:28.000 --> 33:29.620
She's Quinn. Huck will
never stop looking for her,

33:29.620 --> 33:30.790
and...

33:30.790 --> 33:32.750
we need to bury her.

33:49.540 --> 33:51.670
You got what you wanted.

33:51.670 --> 33:54.540
Now let me out.

33:54.540 --> 33:57.040
Mm.

33:59.290 --> 34:01.960
Would you settle
for a glass of wine?

34:01.960 --> 34:04.500
I sure could use one.

34:04.500 --> 34:07.080
I could use some water.

34:12.330 --> 34:15.120
You won't need the chain.

34:34.920 --> 34:36.500
Olivia is a bitch.

34:37.750 --> 34:39.960
It was impressive.

34:39.960 --> 34:41.250
Okay, yeah, it was.

34:41.250 --> 34:42.620
But still...come on.

34:42.620 --> 34:45.460
I am not going to call
my child a bitch.

34:45.460 --> 34:46.750
Fine.

34:46.750 --> 34:48.580
She is, though.

34:48.580 --> 34:49.540
What is it?
Ooh!

34:49.540 --> 34:51.080
Contractions?

34:51.080 --> 34:53.420
Oh, it's nothing.
It's...fine.

34:53.420 --> 34:54.830
Braxton Hicks.
Comes and goes.

34:54.830 --> 34:56.170
Here. Stand up.
I'm fine.

34:56.170 --> 34:59.710
Stand. Up.

35:02.540 --> 35:03.540
Here we go.

35:03.540 --> 35:05.290
Deep breaths.
Like this.

35:09.750 --> 35:11.120
Oh!

35:15.210 --> 35:17.080
These aren't
Braxton Hicks.

35:17.080 --> 35:19.040
What do you mean?

35:19.040 --> 35:20.670
I mean,
my water just broke.

35:20.670 --> 35:22.500
These are...

35:22.500 --> 35:24.460
I'm in labor.
This is labor.

35:24.460 --> 35:26.540
Okay.
Okay. Okay. Okay. Okay.

35:26.540 --> 35:27.580
Okay. Okay.

35:27.580 --> 35:28.920
All right. Come on.

35:28.920 --> 35:30.830
All right.
It's all right.

35:30.830 --> 35:32.040
No. I think --
Ju-- No.

35:32.040 --> 35:33.540
Just -- Just -- Just --
Just relax. Relax.

35:33.540 --> 35:35.620
Sitting is the opposite
of what we should be doing.

35:35.620 --> 35:38.000
We need to get to a hospital.
We need to get Charlie.

35:38.000 --> 35:39.880
Ow!
It'll be fine.

35:39.880 --> 35:41.670
Just be calm.

35:43.120 --> 35:44.710
What are you doing?

35:44.710 --> 35:46.000
We need to leave!

35:46.000 --> 35:47.670
You'll be fine!

35:47.670 --> 35:50.250
Women have had babies
since the beginning of time

35:50.250 --> 35:51.420
without a hospital.

35:51.420 --> 35:52.880
We'll just do this
the old-fashioned way.

35:52.880 --> 35:54.580
No.

35:54.580 --> 35:56.000
Mnh-mnh.
No, no, no.
No.

35:56.000 --> 35:57.420
Ah!

35:57.420 --> 35:59.620
Listen. I know --
I know you're afraid.

35:59.620 --> 36:01.120
I know you're afraid.

36:01.120 --> 36:03.500
It's -- It's okay.
It's okay.

36:03.500 --> 36:05.290
Please.

36:05.290 --> 36:06.670
Please don't.

36:06.670 --> 36:08.420
Please.
I need a hospital.

36:08.420 --> 36:10.880
I need Charlie.

36:10.880 --> 36:12.080
Help.

36:12.080 --> 36:14.000
It's okay, Robin.

36:16.040 --> 36:18.420
Everything's gonna be fine.

36:18.420 --> 36:22.120
Everything's gonna be
just fine.

36:22.120 --> 36:23.250
Aah.

36:23.250 --> 36:27.000
♪♪

36:27.000 --> 36:29.540
Marv: There's been
some misunderstanding.

36:29.540 --> 36:32.330
Montell --
Rowan: I told you.
It's an emergency.

36:32.330 --> 36:34.250
You said
you delivered babies before!

36:34.250 --> 36:35.670
That was in Vietnam!

36:35.670 --> 36:38.000
Quinn.
Open your eyes.

36:38.000 --> 36:39.120
This wouldn't be so hard

36:39.120 --> 36:40.710
if you hadn't
knocked her unconscious.

36:40.710 --> 36:42.000
She needs to be awake!

36:42.000 --> 36:43.710
She needs to push!

36:43.710 --> 36:45.210
There you are.
There she is.

36:45.210 --> 36:46.580
No yelling.

36:46.580 --> 36:48.960
Tell them no yelling
in front of the baby.

36:48.960 --> 36:50.120
Rowan: She's awake.
Tell her what to do.

36:50.120 --> 36:51.960
What's her name?
Christy.

36:51.960 --> 36:53.420
Christy?

36:53.420 --> 36:54.920
I'm gonna need you to push.
Need you to push.

36:54.920 --> 36:56.250
Push?

36:56.250 --> 36:58.920
-It's okay.
-You can do it.

37:01.830 --> 37:03.210
The head is out.

37:03.210 --> 37:04.460
I just need
to pass the shoulders.

37:04.460 --> 37:06.620
Abby: Breathe. Push.

37:06.620 --> 37:07.670
You'll be okay.

37:10.080 --> 37:11.620
Come over here.
Help me.

37:11.620 --> 37:13.380
You're doing great.

37:13.380 --> 37:15.540
Charlie: Robin, look at me.
Look at me.

37:15.540 --> 37:17.040
You're doing so good.

37:17.040 --> 37:19.460
She's gonna be here soon,
and she's gonna be so beautiful.

37:19.460 --> 37:22.210
I've got you.
We've got you.

37:22.210 --> 37:23.500
Quinn:

37:28.620 --> 37:29.880
Oh.
Is that her?!

37:29.880 --> 37:31.420
Is that her?

37:31.420 --> 37:37.420
♪♪

37:38.040 --> 37:40.540
I did it.
I did it.

37:40.540 --> 37:41.830
It's a girl.

37:41.830 --> 37:44.880
Give her to me.

37:44.880 --> 37:47.380
Charlie: You did good, Robin.
Sleep now.

37:47.380 --> 37:49.420
You can see her
when you wake up.

37:50.420 --> 37:53.250
Rowan:

38:04.000 --> 38:05.380
My baby.

38:05.380 --> 38:07.040
Shh, shh, shh, shh.
She's right here.

38:07.040 --> 38:08.170
Is she okay?

38:08.170 --> 38:09.500
She is perfect.

38:16.330 --> 38:17.620
Hi.

38:20.710 --> 38:22.500
Hi, little thing.

38:26.250 --> 38:28.380
Hi.

38:36.460 --> 38:39.580
There was someone else here.
A man.

38:39.580 --> 38:41.170
A dear friend of mine

38:41.170 --> 38:43.750
willing to make
a discreet house call.

38:43.750 --> 38:45.750
A doctor?
That's good.

38:45.750 --> 38:47.670
So she -- She's really
all good

38:47.670 --> 38:48.920
According to my friend

38:48.920 --> 38:50.460
and every checklist
on the Internet, yes.

38:50.460 --> 38:53.290
And you were exquisite.

38:56.540 --> 38:58.580
Hey.

38:58.580 --> 39:01.540
You dressed her and...

39:01.540 --> 39:03.830
diapered her.

39:03.830 --> 39:06.210
And all this stuff
is for us?

39:06.210 --> 39:11.710
This was Liv's room.

39:11.710 --> 39:14.920
You understand you --
you can't go home just yet?

39:14.920 --> 39:18.500
I know.

39:18.500 --> 39:20.580
Liv thinks I'm dead, and
if she finds out I'm not...

39:20.580 --> 39:22.290
You're safe here.

39:22.290 --> 39:24.580
Until we can figure out
how to proceed.

39:24.580 --> 39:27.500
That's...

39:27.500 --> 39:29.880
Thank you.

39:29.880 --> 39:32.710
Now, the little lady
must be hungry,

39:32.710 --> 39:34.290
and that's my cue
to leave.

39:34.290 --> 39:37.080
I have to tidy up
in the basement.

39:37.080 --> 39:39.710
A little girl
in the house.

39:39.710 --> 39:42.000
What a blessing.
What a joy.

39:42.000 --> 39:44.250
You're a good person.

39:49.500 --> 39:51.000
We're all good people

39:51.000 --> 39:53.500
when someone gives us
a chance to be.

39:59.170 --> 40:01.290
Hey.

40:03.290 --> 40:05.790
♪♪

40:37.580 --> 40:41.210
Rowan, there are
enough clothes up there

40:41.210 --> 40:42.580
to get her
through kindergarten.

40:42.580 --> 40:45.000
How long are
you planning on keeping --

40:45.000 --> 40:48.290
Oh, my God.

40:48.290 --> 40:50.670
I'm sorry.

40:50.670 --> 40:52.960
Sorry?

40:52.960 --> 40:55.210
I called you good!

40:55.210 --> 40:58.750
You are
not a good person.

40:58.750 --> 41:01.620
You are a twisted...
Shut up!

41:01.620 --> 41:03.380
...callous, crazy old man

41:03.380 --> 41:04.710
with a bloated corpse
in his basement.

41:04.710 --> 41:08.420
His name is Marvin Heward!

41:08.420 --> 41:11.920
He was a United States Marine.
He served in Vietnam.

41:14.500 --> 41:18.080
He...

41:18.080 --> 41:19.620
was a good person.

41:21.790 --> 41:23.830
He...

41:23.830 --> 41:25.960
was my only friend.

41:25.960 --> 41:28.120
And I killed him.

41:28.120 --> 41:29.420
For you and that baby.

41:32.420 --> 41:35.750
Mothers and children first.

41:35.750 --> 41:37.120
That's the rule.

41:37.120 --> 41:40.750
♪♪

41:40.750 --> 41:44.000
So don't preach to me.

41:44.000 --> 41:46.250
♪♪

41:50.330 --> 41:53.250
Shh.

41:53.250 --> 41:59.250
♪♪

42:03.330 --> 42:06.670
♪♪

42:12.540 --> 42:18.540
♪♪

42:22.540 --> 42:28.540
♪♪

